{"quote": "War is Hell", "page_title": "William Tecumseh Sherman", "page_bio": "William Tecumseh Sherman (8 February 1820 \u2013 14 February 1891) was a United States Army General during the American Civil War. He succeeded Ulysses S. Grant as commander of the Western Theater of the American Civil War of that war in the spring of 1864. He later served as Commanding General of the United States Army (1869\u20131883). He is best known for his destructive Shermans March to the Sea through the state of Georgia and is widely regarded as an early advocate of Total war.", "page_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William Tecumseh Sherman"}